You are working in a course project repository.

Project context:
- Primary language: Python 3
- Typical files: small scripts and CSV data files
- Keep solutions beginner-friendly and readable

Coding preferences:
- Prefer clear, straightforward code over clever optimizations
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Keep functions focused and short when practical
- Add brief docstrings for non-trivial functions
- Use comments sparingly and only where intent is not obvious

Python style:
- Follow PEP 8 conventions
- Keep imports at the top of each file
- Avoid adding new dependencies unless explicitly requested
- Prefer standard library solutions first
- Preserve UTF-8 handling for text and CSV files

Data/file handling:
- Use robust file paths (relative to script location) when reading local files
- Do not modify source CSV files unless explicitly asked
- Validate assumptions about column names before processing data

Git/workflow safety:
- Do not run destructive git commands
- Never rewrite user changes outside requested scope
- Keep edits minimal and targeted to the task

Response behavior:
- Explain changes briefly in plain language
- Include exact run commands when relevant
- If uncertain requirements exist, ask one focused clarification question
